.TH man "31 Oct 2021" "1.0" "simple_shell man page"
.SH NAME
.B hsh
 Holberton School Simple Shell
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh
[command] [options]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The shell is both an interactive command language and a scripting language,
simple_shell is a program that emulates the shell command interpreter.
Traditionally, the Bourne shell program name is sh and its path in the Unix file system hierarchy is /bin/sh.
But a number of compatible work-alikes are also available with various improvements and additional features. 
On many systems, sh may be a symbolic link or hard link to one of these alternatives
.B Overview
The simple shell is a simplified iteration of a command line interpreter.
- FORMAT [ARGUMENT]...
.SH OPTIONS
.I interactive
Example:
$ ./hsh
($) /bin/ls
hsh main.c shell.c
($)
($) exit
$
and
.II non-interactive
Example:
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
hsh main.c shell.c test_ls_2
$
$ cat test_ls_2
/bin/ls
/bin/ls
$
$ cat test_ls_2 | ./hsh
hsh main.c shell.c test_ls_2
hsh main.c shell.c test_ls_2
$
 mode. The user may initiate
./hsh
./hsh
using commands meant to be run by the program.
.SH SEE ALSO
printf
